# GCC 16 dropped the CONST_CAST_TREE / CONST_CAST helpers and changed the
# C++ ABI of internal symbols (e.g. irange::verify_range), so the kernel's
# scripts/gcc-plugins/*.c won't compile, and any .so cached from a gcc-15
# build can't be dlopen'd by gcc-16's cc1. Linux 6.18/6.19 don't carry an
# upstream fix and gcc-plugins are on track for removal upstream anyway.
#
# Of the plugins available in this tree (latent_entropy, randomize_layout,
# stackleak), only LATENT_ENTROPY is enabled by the hardened distconfig,
# and on x86 with RDRAND/RDSEED + jitterentropy + the post-5.18 RNG rework
# its contribution is marginal. STRUCTLEAK-style protection is already
# covered by CONFIG_INIT_STACK_ALL_ZERO (-ftrivial-auto-var-init=zero).
# CONFIG_GCC_PLUGINS is not set
